cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.LG

The paper discusses the privacy risks posed by ambient WiFi signals and proposes defenses against adversarial WiFi sensing. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for user tracking, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.LG). Finally, the proposed defenses involve signal obfuscation and geo-fencing, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
